      <article id="tribute-info">
        <div id="intro"><p>&bull; Sigmund Freud (1856 - 1939) was the creator of the psychoanalysis. &bull;</p></div>
        <p><u>These are some facts about his life:</u></p>
        <p>
          <ul>
            <li>He was born to Galician Jewish parents in Austria in 1856.</li>
            <li>He qualified as a doctor in medicine in 1881 at the University of Vienna.</li>
            <li>In founding psychoanalysis, he developed new methods and techniques such as free association and transference.</li>
            <li>He used the pacient's dreams, jokes and other things that science believed unimportant for treatment.</li>
            <li>His research led him to believe that traumas were originated in the patient's childhood.</li>
            <li>He established several defense mechanisms like represion that make people act like they do.</li>
            <li>In 1838 he left Austria to escape the Nazis, due to his jewish roots.</li>
            <li>He died in exile in the United Kindom in 1939.</li>
          </ul>
      </p>
        <blockquote id="quote">
          <p>Where id was, there ego shall be.</p>
          <cite>-- Sigmund Freud</cite>
        </blockquote>
        <hr>
        <p>If you want to know more about his life, feel free to do so in <a id="tribute-link" href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Sigmund_Freud" target="_blank">Wikipedia</a>.</p>
      </article>
